<br>
The level 55 cap on mobs seems to be outdated considering new zones like Cazic Thule are going to be more common.<br>
<br>
We need to find some way to allow us to stun mobs but not trivialise them with permanent stun. We've all done the 4 paladin group with stun bracer and seen what it can do. Do that on a 55+ mob and you can make it very safe to get quality exp.<br>
<br>
What we really need is some form of compromise. Something that won't trivialise the encounter but something that also isn't futile and a waste of time.<br>
<br>
I don't know of a solution. If it was easy we would have it already.<br>
<br>
For me personally, the ability to interrupt a level 55-60 mob would make me happy. A very slight chance to interrupt a level 61+ mob would be awesome. Id prefer to be able to channel debuff an uber mob, and let the raid using push tactics interrupt it. Code already exists with spell effects like feeblemind from the Overfiend. If we could cast that on mobs, its going to give us the capability to interrupt level 61 mobs but you are going to need your tanks all pushing in the same direction.<br>
